18/11/2005
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski met on Thursday (17 November) with Slovenian counterpart Janez Jansa in a bid to learn more about the Slovenian experience with Euro-Atlantic integration. 
The officials also discussed ways to strengthen bilateral co-operation, with a special emphasis on economic relations. 
On Friday, Buckovski visited the Macedonian-Slovenian business forum. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 17/11/05)
